This paper deals with the problem of designing decentralized schemes for coded caching, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper proposes a translation scheme that converts a centralized scheme into a decentralized one, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and system and control theory (cs.SY) aspects. The paper also discusses the dynamics of user arrival and departure, which involves distributed systems (cs.DS) concepts.
